Step 1. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Main Business Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
• Here, beginning AR = 0 and ending AR = 1,716,911.17, so the average AR = (0 + 1,716,911.17) / 2 = 858,455.585.  
• Main Business Revenue = 3,025,437.82  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = 3,025,437.82 / 858,455.585 ≈ 3.52  

Step 2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio and Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Both ratios in these examples are calculated as: Operating Cash Flow / Total Current Liabilities.  
• Operating Cash Flow (from the cash flow statement) = 116,257.19  
• Total Current Liabilities (end balance) = 967,271.87  
• Ratio = 116,257.19 / 967,271.87 ≈ 0.12  

Step 3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• Total Assets at the beginning: 13,000,000.00 and at the end: 14,930,535.06 so the average = (13,000,000 + 14,930,535.06) / 2 ≈ 13,965,267.53  
• Total Revenue = 3,025,437.82  
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = 3,025,437.82 / 13,965,267.53 ≈ 0.22  

Step 4. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Formula: Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
• Here, Total Liabilities are represented by Total Current Liabilities = 967,271.87  
• Total Owner's Equity (end) = 13,963,263.19  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 967,271.87 / 13,963,263.19 ≈ 0.07  

Thus, the final solution in JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "3.52",
    "operating cash flow ratio": "0.12",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "0.12",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.22",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.07"
  }
}
